use double quotes (") inside of single quotes (') to indicate a quote within your string
    can also use backticks (`) to allow for var use within strings

template literal `hello ${world}`

strings are primitive, meaning they are immutable

chars are zero indexed, you can call each char in a string by counting from 0 to the position you want

string methods
    concat
    includes
    indexOf negative num = non-existent
    lastIndexOf
    replace
    startsWith
    endsWith
    substring
    toLower
    toUpper
    trim

both sides of an && statement must be "truthy"

